Text.Value: It was no mean feat to make nice with the sourest puss in the city, by the way. It took years for Astele and I to trust one another.
The Absolute threatens thousands - the entire Coast - and still you risked much to help one man. I should berate you, but... I can only say thank you.
Hm? Boo would know the meaning of your meaningful glances.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Shot of Minsc holding Boo up in his palm, facing him as if they were discussing something. Both look at us as suspiciously, as if we're interrupting.
EditorData.NodeContext:
Breaking off as if we're interrupting something. 'Hm?' is followed by a Boo squeak, then Minsc's next line.
Sample: Boo_Talketive_MediumPitch_09

Text.Value: You reasons were your own but, whether you meant for it or not, your fight is our fight. Both of us, to the very end.
Don't thank me just yet. Minsc and Keene are sure to give you some headaches.
For the moment he - and I - are your problem. So lead the way - we are yours to command.
I think you might have made a terrible, terrible mistake.
Don't go getting sentimental on me now, Harper.
Bringing those two together might have been your greatest service to the city, or your worst. Time will tell.
I think you will find that Boo is the added bonus - Minsc is just here to carry him into battle. But you are right to focus on the fight.
While I wish Minsc had seen reason at the Guildhall, even so...
Chasing rumour halfway around the city and back. Crossing the Guild, wading through filth, defying the one creature upon whom your very life depends.
Ah, those misty eyes are just age. I feel myself growing older as we stand here. So:
All... for this.
Yes, it was. If you need confirmation of my gratitude, only look - here I stand, awaiting orders. So:
He is an ass. I can make no promises beyond that. But even so:
Now we can focus our efforts on the remaining Chosen.
But I think she can handle the worst of his excesses. She had best believe that he will very much handle hers.
Hm. None of that was a thank you.
Lead the way. We're yours to command.
Do not take that tone with me, rodent. Fine. All three of us, then.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Interrupted by an indignant Boo squeak - she points a warning finger out of shot, then corrects herself.
EditorData.NodeContext:
Jaheira responds to Boo squeaking in objection at being left out (he's off-screen).
Pointing at him warningly (off-screen, so front-right is fine), then turning back to player with a smile and correction.
Sample squeak: Boo_Talketive_SqueakyHighPitch_19

Text.Value: All for a madman and his rodent.
Don't thank me. It's the cult I'm focused on - anything else is an added bonus.
Minsc will be an asset, I'm sure.

Synopsis: Jaheira's default dialogue. Topics range from her past life to her current goals as they develop. Unless otherwise stated, her tone is confident and to the point. She's a seasoned adventurer with a sardonic sense of humour - and a little less cynical than she might present herself to be.
